				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Twilight of the Divine Right: With Fire and Sword – Scenario Book 2: The Deluge, 1632–1660" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>This second book covers the battles during the period sometimes called the &amp;lsquo;Deluge&amp;rsquo;. The 'Deluge' period saw the Polish Lithuanian Commonwealth attacked by many armies. The booklet concentrates on the war of 1648 -1657 against the Cossack rebellion under Khmelnytsky. Also the campaigns of 1655 &amp;ndash; 1660 is against the Swedes. In addition the Russians war against the Commonwealth in the Smolensk War of 1632 &amp;ndash; 1634 is also covered. The first war that Russia started to modernise it's army. It is common for allies to be present on one or both sides in these battles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The booklet features 8 scenarios from 6 historical battles and campaigns.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Battles featured:&amp;#10;Smolensk, 1633&amp;#10;Pyliavsti, 1648&amp;#10;Berestecko, 1651&amp;#10;Batoh, 1652&amp;#10;Zarnow, 1655 &amp;#10;Warsaw, 1656&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
